---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/page.astro";
import Container from "@components/container.astro";
import Head from "@components/head.astro";
import Navbar from "@components/navbar.astro";
import Footer from "@components/footer.astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import type { ImageMetadata } from "astro";

const images = import.meta.glob<{ default: ImageMetadata }>(
  "/src/assets/portfolio/*.{jpeg,jpg,png,gif,webp}"
);

const projectTitle = "MindSpark";
const projectDate = "Spring 2026";
const projectTags = [
  "Swift",
  "SwiftUI",
  "Anthropic Claude API",
  "AI",
  "Combine",
  "async/await",
  "MVVM",
  "XCTest",
  "AVFoundation",
];
const githubUrl = "https://github.com/kdvasquez/mindspark";

const screenshots = [
  {
    src: "/src/assets/portfolio/mindspark1.png",
    alt: "MindSpark home screen with learning modes",
    caption: "Home Dashboard",
  },
  {
    src: "/src/assets/portfolio/mindspark3.png",
    alt: "Math Blitz multiplication practice screen",
    caption: "Math Blitz",
  },
  {
    src: "/src/assets/portfolio/mindspark4.png",
    alt: "AI-generated hint shown during a math question",
    caption: "AI Hint",
  },
  {
    src: "/src/assets/portfolio/mindspark5.png",
    alt: "Story Quest topic picker screen",
    caption: "Story Topic Picker",
  },
  {
    src: "/src/assets/portfolio/mindspark6.png",
    alt: "AI-generated reading passage with comprehension questions",
    caption: "Story Quest",
  },
  {
    src: "/src/assets/portfolio/mindspark2.png",
    alt: "MindSpark results screen with stars and progress summary",
    caption: "Results and Progress",
  },
];
---

<PageLayout>
  <head>
    <Head title={projectTitle} permalink="/projects/mindspark" />
  </head>

  <body>
    <Navbar />
    <Container>
      <article class="project-detail">
        <header class="project-header">
          <h1>{projectTitle}</h1>
          <p class="project-date">{projectDate}</p>
        </header>

        <section class="project-section tldr">
          <div class="tldr-layout">
            <div class="tldr-info">
              <h2>At a Glance</h2>
              <p class="tagline">
                An AI-powered iOS learning app that combines multiplication practice with custom
                reading comprehension stories for elementary students.
              </p>

              <div class="tldr-grid">
                <div class="tldr-item">
                  <span class="tldr-label">Role</span>
                  <span class="tldr-value">Solo designer and iOS developer</span>
                </div>
                <div class="tldr-item">
                  <span class="tldr-label">Tech Stack</span>
                  <span class="tldr-value">
                    <strong>Language:</strong> Swift<br />
                    <strong>UI/Apple frameworks:</strong> SwiftUI, Combine, AVFoundation<br />
                    <strong>AI/API:</strong> Anthropic Claude API, JSON prompt contracts<br />
                    <strong>Persistence:</strong> UserDefaults, Codable<br />
                    <strong>Architecture:</strong> MVVM, service protocol injection<br />
                    <strong>Testing:</strong> XCTest, XCUITest
                  </span>
                </div>
                <div class="tldr-item">
                  <span class="tldr-label">AI Status</span>
                  <span class="tldr-value">
                    Live Claude API integration is implemented behind a mockable service layer. The
                    app currently defaults to mock responses for development and UI testing.
                  </span>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="project-links">
                {githubUrl && (
                  <a href={githubUrl} target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="btn-link">
                    View on GitHub
                  </a>
                )}
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="tldr-video">
              <video autoplay loop muted playsinline class="demo-video">
                <source src="/mindspark-demo.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
              </video>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="project-section">
          <h2>Problem and Motivation</h2>
          <p>
            I wanted to build a learning app that felt more adaptive than a static quiz for my students to try out. 
            Many practice apps give students the same questions and the same feedback no matter what they struggle
            with, which can make mistakes feel repetitive instead of useful. MindSpark explores how AI
            can make practice feel more personal, encouraging, and responsive.
          </p>
          <p>
            The project was also a way to bring several iOS concepts together in one product-like
            experience: SwiftUI state management, async networking, testable game logic, persistent
            progress tracking, read-aloud support, and a kid-friendly interface.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="project-section">
          <h2>Overview</h2>
          <p>
            MindSpark has two learning modes. Math Blitz helps students practice multiplication facts
            through timed multiple-choice rounds, streak scoring, hints, mastery tracking, and results
            feedback. Story Quest lets students choose a topic and receive an AI-generated reading
            passage with comprehension questions and gentle explanations for wrong answers.
          </p>
          <p>
            Behind the interface, the app uses a protocol-based AI service so the real Claude API can
            be swapped with a mock service during development and tests. That made it possible to build
            loading states, error handling, and UI flows without depending on live API calls.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="project-section">
          <h2>App in Action</h2>
          <div class="screenshot-grid">
            {screenshots.map((item) => {
              const imageLoader = images[item.src];
              return (
                <div class="screenshot">
                  {imageLoader ? (
                    <Image src={imageLoader()} alt={item.alt} quality={95} />
                  ) : (
                    <div class="screenshot-placeholder">
                      <span>{item.caption}</span>
                    </div>
                  )}
                  <p class="caption">{item.caption}</p>
                </div>
              );
            })}
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="project-section">
          <h2>Core Features</h2>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon">AI</div>
            <div class="feature-content">
              <h3>AI-Generated Learning Support</h3>
              <p>
                The app can call Claude to generate math hints, reading passages, comprehension
                questions, wrong-answer explanations, difficulty recommendations, and parent-friendly
                progress summaries.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon">×</div>
            <div class="feature-content">
              <h3>Math Blitz Practice Mode</h3>
              <p>
                Students answer timed multiplication questions with streak-based scoring, limited
                hints, animated answer states, and a results screen that highlights weak spots.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon">Aa</div>
            <div class="feature-content">
              <h3>Story Quest Reading Mode</h3>
              <p>
                Students choose a topic, read a short story, and answer
                multiple-choice comprehension questions generated from the passage.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon">↗</div>
            <div class="feature-content">
              <h3>Progress and Mastery Tracking</h3>
              <p>
                UserDefaults and Codable models persist daily stars, total sessions, streaks, and
                multiplication mastery records so progress carries across app launches.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="feature-row">
            <div class="feature-icon">♬</div>
            <div class="feature-content">
              <h3>Read-Aloud Support</h3>
              <p>
                An AVSpeechSynthesizer service provides text-to-speech for Story Quest, making the app
                more approachable for younger learners and students who benefit from audio support.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="project-section">
          <h2>Tech Stack and Technical Decisions</h2>

          <div class="highlight-card">
            <h3>Protocol-Based AI Service</h3>
            <p>
              I created an <code>AIServiceProtocol</code> with both real and mock implementations. This
              made the app easier to test, kept UI development fast, and separated the product behavior
              from the availability and cost of live API calls.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="highlight-card">
            <h3>Structured JSON Prompt Contracts</h3>
            <p>
              Each AI prompt asks for valid JSON matching a Swift <code>Codable</code> model. That kept
              the model output predictable enough to decode into typed app data instead of treating AI
              responses as loose strings.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="highlight-card">
            <h3>SwiftUI MVVM State Management</h3>
            <p>
              I kept game and story logic in <code>GameViewModel</code> and <code>StoryViewModel</code>,
              with views observing published state. That made the learning flows easier to reason about
              and kept UI code focused on presentation.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="highlight-card">
            <h3>Pure Swift Logic for Testability</h3>
            <p>
              The multiplication generator and session scoring logic are independent of SwiftUI, which
              allowed me to cover them with focused XCTest cases.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="project-section">
          <h2>Challenges and What I Learned</h2>

          <div class="challenge">
            <h3>Designing AI Features That Support Learning</h3>
            <p>
              I had to think beyond simply adding an API call. The prompts needed to produce responses
              that were age-appropriate, encouraging, short enough for the UI, and structured enough for
              the app to parse reliably.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="challenge">
            <h3>Keeping the App Testable Without Live AI Calls</h3>
            <p>
              Live AI calls are slow, cost money, and can vary from run to run. Adding a mock AI service
              let me test the full interface and loading states while still keeping the real integration
              ready behind the same protocol.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="challenge">
            <h3>Managing Timed Game State in SwiftUI</h3>
            <p>
              Math Blitz uses a Combine timer, answer state, score updates, hint loading, and automatic
              question advancement. Building that flow reinforced the importance of a clear state
              machine instead of scattering game state across views.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="challenge">
            <h3>Balancing Delight with Accessibility</h3>
            <p>
              Because the audience is elementary students, the interface needed to feel playful without
              becoming confusing. Text-to-speech, settings, readable cards, and simple interaction
              patterns helped keep the app approachable.
            </p>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="project-section">
          <h2>Results</h2>
          <div class="stats">
            <div class="stat-item">
              <span class="stat-number">5</span>
              <span class="stat-label">AI-powered learning features implemented</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-item">
              <span class="stat-number">2</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Practice modes: Math Blitz and Story Quest</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-item">
              <span class="stat-number">3</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Persistent progress systems: stars, streaks, mastery</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stat-item">
              <span class="stat-number">15+</span>
              <span class="stat-label">Unit and UI test cases covering core flows</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <section class="project-section">
          <h2>Future Improvements</h2>
          <ul>
            <li>
              Move the Anthropic API key behind a lightweight backend proxy before any production
              release.
            </li>
            <li>
              Add parent and teacher dashboards for viewing progress across multiple learners.
            </li>
            <li>
              Use CloudKit or a backend database to sync progress across devices.
            </li>
            <li>
              Add adaptive practice sessions that automatically prioritize weak multiplication facts.
            </li>
            <li>
              Input little games the student can playing after completing a mission for more inspiration.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </section>
      </article>

      <div class="back-button">
        <a href="/portfolio">← Back to Portfolio</a>
      </div>
    </Container>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</PageLayout>

<style lang="scss">
  .back-button {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    a {
      display: inline-flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 0.5rem;
      color: var(--med);
      text-decoration: none;
      font-weight: 500;
      padding: 0.5rem 0;
      transition: all 0.2s;
      box-shadow: none;
      &:hover {
        color: var(--black);
        background: none;
        transform: translateX(-4px);
      }
    }
  }

  .project-detail {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .project-header {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .project-date {
    color: var(--med);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .tagline {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--med);
    margin: 0.25rem 0 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  .project-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .btn-link {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    background-color: var(--med);
    color: var(--white);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-radius: 4px;
    transition: background-color 0.3s;
    font-weight: bold;
    box-shadow: var(--smalldrop);
    &:hover {
      background-color: var(--black);
      color: var(--white);
    }
  }

  .tldr {
    background-color: var(--light);
    padding: 1.75rem;
    border-radius: 12px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--med);
  }

  .tldr-layout {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    align-items: center;
    margin-top: 1rem;

    @media (max-width: 700px) {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .tldr-grid {
    display: grid;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .tldr-item {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.2rem;
  }

  .tldr-label {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: var(--med);
  }

  .tldr-value {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--black);
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .tldr-video {
    text-align: center;

    .demo-video {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 240px;
      border-radius: 18px;
      box-shadow: var(--carddrop);
      display: block;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
  }

  .project-section {
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    h2 {
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
      padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--light);
    }
    h3 {
      margin-top: 1.5rem;
      margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    }
    p {
      line-height: 1.7;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }
    ul {
      line-height: 1.8;
      margin-left: 1.5rem;
      li {
        margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      }
    }
    code {
      background: var(--light);
      padding: 0.1rem 0.4rem;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.88em;
    }
  }

  .feature-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
    margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
  }

  .feature-icon {
    width: 2.15rem;
    min-width: 2.15rem;
    height: 2.15rem;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    margin-top: 0.1rem;
    border-radius: 999px;
    background: var(--light);
    color: var(--med);
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .feature-content {
    h3 {
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    p {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
  }

  .highlight-card {
    background: var(--white);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--med);
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: var(--photodrop);
    h3 {
      margin-top: 0;
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
      font-size: 1rem;
      color: var(--med);
    }
    p {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
  }

  .challenge {
    background-color: var(--white);
    border-left: 4px solid var(--med);
    padding: 1.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: var(--photodrop);
    h3 {
      margin-top: 0;
      color: var(--med);
    }
    p:last-child {
      margin-bottom: 0;
    }
  }

  .screenshot-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.25rem;
    margin-top: 1.5rem;

    @media (max-width: 600px) {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .screenshot {
    text-align: center;
    img,
    .screenshot-placeholder {
      width: 100%;
      aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
      border-radius: 8px;
      box-shadow: var(--carddrop);
    }
    img {
      height: auto;
      object-fit: cover;
    }
    .screenshot-placeholder {
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      justify-content: center;
      padding: 1rem;
      background: var(--light);
      color: var(--med);
      font-weight: 700;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .caption {
      margin-top: 0.4rem;
      font-size: 0.8rem;
      color: var(--med);
      font-style: italic;
    }
  }

  .stats {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(160px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 2rem 0;
  }

  .stat-item {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background-color: var(--light);
    border-radius: 8px;
    .stat-number {
      display: block;
      font-size: 2.5rem;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: var(--med);
      margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    }
    .stat-label {
      display: block;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      color: var(--black);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .screenshot-grid,
    .stats {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
    }

    .feature-row {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>